### Branches

Right now the repo has `main` and `Teresa`. One branch is cleaner — the convention for this kind of project is to work on feature branches and merge into `main`, then delete the branch after merging. If Teresa's work is already merged into `main`, the `Teresa` branch can just be deleted. If it isn't merged yet, open a pull request → merge → delete.
